<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5102842>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. Phlaeopterus species, habitus. A) P. bakerensis, female (UAMObs:Ento:233271), B) P. castaneus, female" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5102842/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5102855>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Distributions of Phlaeopterus species based on all georeferenced specimen records. A) P. bakerensis, B) P. castaneus. Grey dots represent localities where at least one Phlaeopterus species, but not the species of interest, was collected. Red dots represent localities where the species of interest was collected. In B, red triangles represent localities of P. castaneus castaneus, red squares represent localities of P. castaneus cascadiensis, and green stars represent areas of overlap of the two subspecies." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5102855/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5102875>
    dc:description "Fig. 22. Phlaeopterus species, aedeagi (left = ventral view; right = dorsal view of median lobe). A) P. castaneus castaneus, B–D) variation in P. cavicollis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5102875/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

